Uitenhage police are investigating the mysterious death of a nine-year-old girl after she allegedly ingested sleeping pills. CAPE TOWN - Uitenhage police are investigating the mysterious death of a nine-year-old girl after she allegedly ingested sleeping pills.Local news outlets in Jeffreys Bay are reporting that the girl died after her mother allegedly placed the pills in her milkshake before going to bed earlier this week.According to News24, the mother reportedly tried to commit suicide after realising her daughter was dead.Police spokesperson Gerda Swarts says she cannot confirm these details, but says the mother is currently in hospital and has not been arrested. At this stage I can only confirm that the SAPS has opened an inquest which will be investigated. It s being alleged that the child obtained sleeping tablets in a certain manner. We are currently investigating the matter. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)